'''Tindark''' was a [[platform city]] located on the opposite side of [[Cularin/Legends|Cularin]] from [[Mikish]]. It was home to the [[Metatheran Cartel]]'s and [[SoroSuub Corporation/Legends|SoroSuub's]] regional offices on Cularin. Thus, it received a lot of traffic, but it was a quieter city in attitude than other platform cities like Mikish. The Metatheran Cartel owned part of the spaceport and also vast storage houses.<ref name="l">''[[Living Force Campaign Guide]]''</ref>

Tindark's police force did not have a lot of training or high-end equipment, but they attempted to overcome this by high visibility. The police commissioner was even known to dress up civilians in uniform and send them on patrol. The police did not patrol around the Cartel's storage houses, which nonetheless had never been robbed. It was believed that the Cartel had some [[Droideka/Legends|droidekas]] from their [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation]] days which patrolled their properties.<ref name="l" />

In [[40 BBY/Legends|40 BBY]], the baron administrator of Tindark, [[Piklin Katt]], was assassinated. He was murdered in his bed. No one knew whom he had angered, but his successor was inspired to be very cautious in his dealings.<ref name="l" />

Notable inhabitants of Tindark around [[31 BBY/Legends|31 BBY]] included [[Kyun Squnn]], the second administrator of the [[SoroSuub Corporation/Legends|SoroSuub Corporation]] regional offices; and [[Dirneele]], a club dancer.<ref name="l" />

